in formula (a3-1), R31 and R32 each independently represent a hydrogen atom, alkyl, alkenyl, alkynyl, aryl, or heterocyclyl, or R31 and R32 may be joined together to form a ring structure, L31 represents a linking group, and A-represents an anion-containing structure; Y3 represents a single bond, or a divalent linking group selected from the group consisting of -CO-, -O-, -NH-, a divalent aliphatic group, a divalent aromatic group and a combination thereof; the asterisk (*) indicates the point of attachment to the main chain of the polymer compound;

